Cell Quality Effects

I am testing the quality effects, since it could be a source of error and potentially biased the predicted gwRR if some mice had bad technical noise.

The the plots below, each point is a single mouses mean MLH1 count per cell across each quality score bin.

These plots show that generally there is a positive relationship between good quality (1) and more MLH1 counts.

I should focus on addressing if there are differences in the relationship of quality-MLH1 counts across sexes.

Age Effect (male)

Some papers have documented age effects for male genome-wide recombination rate [@zelazowski2017age].

The initial analysis uses plots. This should be double checked with a general linear model as well.

I made 3 models for 3 groupings of mice, dom, musc.high and musc.low

\[mouse .mean CO ~=~ age + strain + \varepsilon\]
